[{node={text=Djengart pass, chinese boarder, by ¬©Ella Maillart, estate of @elyseemusee , swiss photographer, 1903-1997. Photography became, quite naturally, for Ella Maillart, the prolongation of her gaze, and she made a great use of it. Her apparatus was in a sense her notebook, a day-to-day logbook, with the vision of a modern, independent and unconventional woman. Ella Maillart did not exhibit her photographs at the time of their realization, using them only to illustrate her travel stories, her lectures and the many articles she wrote for the press. The presentation of these photographs amazes today: Time is restored, a whole world disappeared or forgotten resurfaced. In 1989, Ella Maillart entrusted her photographic archives to the Mus√©e de l'Elys√©e in Lausanne, which dedicated to this exceptional ensemble several major exhibitions.
‚Äî

On his first trip to Egypt in 1958, Ren√© Burri discovered the pyramid of Saqqara. Burri grew up among the alpine mountains of Switzerland, so he was instinctively drawn to these prodigious ancient constructions from the hand of man. He saw them as mountains in the desert, but without the snow.

Next to the age-old symbols of Egypt, the Pyramids and the camel, the Ramses car has made its appearance on the modern Egyptian scene.

edge_media_to_caption.edges: [{node={text=By ¬©Iris Hutegger, swiss photographer. ‚ÄúAbove all, I am a sculptor‚Äù says Iris Hutegger. Although her work starts with a camera. She became an artist in her thirties. From a certain distance, her artworks look like colored pencil drawings. But as you get closer, you can perceive the grain of the black and white photograph, and also hundreds of threads, overlapping on the image. We can now understand that the color comes from the threads which embroidered the image and added a third dimension to it.}}]

edge_media_to_caption.edges:
[{node={text=CONQUISTADOR - Nicolas Savary 
Available at bookstores

Photography project inspired by the archive of Louis de Boccard (1866-1956), a Swiss explorer who settled in Argentina in 1889 and worked as a curator at the Museo de La Plata. In the course of his travels in Argentina, Paraguay, and Brazil, he assembled an enormous collection of photographs and postcards, of great historical and anthropological value, which he entitled "Collections of the explorer Ls. de Boccard." The Swiss photographer Nicolas Savary proposes a contemporary focus on the collection. 
This photobook serves as the catalogue of a major exhibition at the Mus√©e de l'√âlys√©e and the Mus√©e gru√©rien in Switzerland.
#conquistador #photography #elyseemusee #editorialrm #documentaryphotography #photobook #fotolibro #contemporaryphotography #nicolassavary}}]

[{node={text=Contact Press Images is overjoyed to announce that our contributor, Matthias Bruggmann has been named the recipient of the second Prix Elysee awarded by an international jury of art and photography experts and the Elysee Museum, Lausanne, Switzerland, at the museum's Nuit des images, Saturday evening. One of the most important awards in photography in Europe, we are humbled by Matt's association with Contact and thrilled for him and this astounding recognition of his work.
Matt says about the project: "It attempts to bring to western viewers, a visceral comprehension of the intangible violence that underlies conflict." The project, comprised of some existing imagery and work to be executed during 2017 will result in a book to be published in 2018. 
For more info surf to: www.prixelysee.ch/en/
